; cerci, 
<number box="[1341,1377,1048,1074]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="3.1">3.1</number>
–4.0. General coloration as male, eggs yellowish white. Metasternal black marks thinner and longer than in male. Wings darker than in male, membrane slightly tinged with yellow, longitudinal and cross veins shaded with brownish, more strongly on C, Sc and R 
<number box="[627,635,1176,1190]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="1.0">1</number>
veins; R 
<number box="[741,749,1176,1190]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="3.0">3</number>
and short intercalary vein before it present on fore wings. Brownish shading on body as in male except slightly paler on abdominal sterna; intersegmental membrane between sterna VII–VIII paler than the rest, sternum VIII with parastyli receptors located submedially (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 40" captionStartId="15.[151,269,1854,1878]" captionTargetBox="[191,1384,197,1829]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[180,1408,197,1829]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 40. Tortopus arenales. 31, male head, d. v.; 32, male abdominal terga VI – VII; 33, male abdominal sterna VII – VIII; 34, male mesofurcasternal plates; 35, female abdominal sternum VIII; 36, male genitalia, v. v.; 37, same, l. v.; 38, penes after treatment with potash; 39 – 40, detail of apex of forceps." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195437/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Figs. 35</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[195,270,1274,1300]" captionStart="FIGURES 67 – 72" captionStartId="25.[151,269,1458,1482]" captionTargetBox="[187,1399,197,1432]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[187,1399,197,1433]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURES 67 – 72. SEM photographs. Tortopus igaranus: 67, egg, general view; 68, egg, detail of convex side; 69, egg, detail of concave side. Tortopus arenales: 70, female abdominal sternum VIII; 71, same, detail of sockets; 72, eggs." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195442/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
70– 
<number box="[242,270,1274,1300]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="71.0">71</number>
</figureCitation>
) and strongly shaded gray. Cerci whitish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,152,1636]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Eggs (
<figureCitation box="[275,366,1312,1338]" captionStart="FIGURES 67 – 72" captionStartId="25.[151,269,1458,1482]" captionTargetBox="[187,1399,197,1432]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[187,1399,197,1433]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURES 67 – 72. SEM photographs. Tortopus igaranus: 67, egg, general view; 68, egg, detail of convex side; 69, egg, detail of concave side. Tortopus arenales: 70, female abdominal sternum VIII; 71, same, detail of sockets; 72, eggs." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195442/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Fig. 
<number box="[332,366,1312,1338]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="72.0">72</number>
</figureCitation>
). Suboval, no attachment structures. Length, 
<number box="[908,952,1312,1338]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="400.0">400</number>
µm; width, 
<number box="[1102,1205,1312,1338]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="337.5" valueMax="345.0" valueMin="330.0">330–345</number>
µm. The relatively thick covering of the egg is relatively smooth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,152,1636]" box="[198,804,1386,1412]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Etymology: from the 
<typeStatus box="[451,502,1386,1412]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">type</typeStatus>
locality, Estero 
<taxonomicName box="[692,800,1386,1412]" class="Insecta" family="Polymitarcyidae" genus="Tortopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arenales">Arenales</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,152,1636]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Discussion and diagnosis. 
<taxonomicName box="[510,721,1424,1449]" class="Insecta" family="Polymitarcyidae" genus="Tortopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arenales" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[510,721,1424,1449]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Tortopus arenales</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[729,820,1424,1450]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be separated from all other species of the genus by the following combination of characters: 
<number box="[715,729,1461,1487]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="1.0">1</number>
) fore wing length 10.0– 
<quantity box="[1039,1148,1461,1487]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.17" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" unit="mm" value="11.7">11.7 mm</quantity>
(male), 
<quantity box="[1256,1436,1461,1487]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.285" metricValueMax="1.45" metricValueMin="1.1199999999999999" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" unit="mm" value="12.85" valueMax="14.5" valueMin="11.2">11.2–14.5 mm</quantity>
(female); 
<number box="[267,283,1498,1524]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="2.0">2</number>
) parastyli with relatively wide base, rest very thin and acute, as long as pedestal (
<figureCitation box="[1256,1389,1498,1524]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 40" captionStartId="15.[151,269,1854,1878]" captionTargetBox="[191,1384,197,1829]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[180,1408,197,1829]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 40. Tortopus arenales. 31, male head, d. v.; 32, male abdominal terga VI – VII; 33, male abdominal sterna VII – VIII; 34, male mesofurcasternal plates; 35, female abdominal sternum VIII; 36, male genitalia, v. v.; 37, same, l. v.; 38, penes after treatment with potash; 39 – 40, detail of apex of forceps." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195437/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Fig. 
<number box="[1311,1389,1498,1524]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="36.5" valueMax="37.0" valueMin="36.0">36–37</number>
</figureCitation>
); 
<number box="[1411,1426,1498,1524]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="3.0">3</number>
) ventral knob well developed (
<figureCitation box="[500,588,1536,1562]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 40" captionStartId="15.[151,269,1854,1878]" captionTargetBox="[191,1384,197,1829]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[180,1408,197,1829]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 40. Tortopus arenales. 31, male head, d. v.; 32, male abdominal terga VI – VII; 33, male abdominal sterna VII – VIII; 34, male mesofurcasternal plates; 35, female abdominal sternum VIII; 36, male genitalia, v. v.; 37, same, l. v.; 38, penes after treatment with potash; 39 – 40, detail of apex of forceps." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195437/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Fig. 
<number box="[555,588,1536,1562]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="36.0">36</number>
</figureCitation>
); 
<number box="[609,625,1536,1562]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="4.0">4</number>
) penes relatively wide at base (fused portion), not strongly expanded distally (
<figureCitation box="[255,345,1573,1599]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 40" captionStartId="15.[151,269,1854,1878]" captionTargetBox="[191,1384,197,1829]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[180,1408,197,1829]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 40. Tortopus arenales. 31, male head, d. v.; 32, male abdominal terga VI – VII; 33, male abdominal sterna VII – VIII; 34, male mesofurcasternal plates; 35, female abdominal sternum VIII; 36, male genitalia, v. v.; 37, same, l. v.; 38, penes after treatment with potash; 39 – 40, detail of apex of forceps." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195437/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Fig. 
<number box="[311,345,1573,1599]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="36.0">36</number>
</figureCitation>
); 
<number box="[367,382,1573,1599]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="5.0">5</number>
) female sockets with oblique opening (
<figureCitation box="[855,943,1573,1599]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 40" captionStartId="15.[151,269,1854,1878]" captionTargetBox="[191,1384,197,1829]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[180,1408,197,1829]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 40. Tortopus arenales. 31, male head, d. v.; 32, male abdominal terga VI – VII; 33, male abdominal sterna VII – VIII; 34, male mesofurcasternal plates; 35, female abdominal sternum VIII; 36, male genitalia, v. v.; 37, same, l. v.; 38, penes after treatment with potash; 39 – 40, detail of apex of forceps." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195437/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[956,1036,1573,1599]" captionStart="FIGURES 67 – 72" captionStartId="25.[151,269,1458,1482]" captionTargetBox="[187,1399,197,1432]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[187,1399,197,1433]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURES 67 – 72. SEM photographs. Tortopus igaranus: 67, egg, general view; 68, egg, detail of convex side; 69, egg, detail of concave side. Tortopus arenales: 70, female abdominal sternum VIII; 71, same, detail of sockets; 72, eggs." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195442/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
70– 
<number box="[1006,1036,1573,1599]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="71.0">71</number>
</figureCitation>
); and 
<number box="[1107,1122,1573,1599]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="6.0">6</number>
) a relatively dark species, shading on occiput forming a profuse anastomosed pattern (
<figureCitation box="[853,939,1610,1636]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 40" captionStartId="15.[151,269,1854,1878]" captionTargetBox="[191,1384,197,1829]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[180,1408,197,1829]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 40. Tortopus arenales. 31, male head, d. v.; 32, male abdominal terga VI – VII; 33, male abdominal sterna VII – VIII; 34, male mesofurcasternal plates; 35, female abdominal sternum VIII; 36, male genitalia, v. v.; 37, same, l. v.; 38, penes after treatment with potash; 39 – 40, detail of apex of forceps." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195437/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Fig. 
<number box="[907,939,1610,1636]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="31.0">31</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
